content:
Have categories enriched in a promonoidal category been considered before?

(I don't have anything in mind to do with these, I'm just curious since this seems a natural thing to consider)
Hmm, interesting - I've never seen that. Did you check that the concept makes sense? E.g.,do you get a category of categories enriched in a promonoidal category, and functors between these?
I think this is probably a special case of categories enriched in a multicategory.
@John Baez Not really; I was mainly hoping that maybe this might have been worked out somewhere in the literature already
